\N<Segi>Father... Mother...
\N<Segi>...
That wasn't just bravado or mere spite towards Zuuteruka.
That's... a message for me. Those words are meant for me.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Yuia>Segi... I'm going...! I've had enough of this... I'll kill
them all...!!

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia... you mustn't. You can't just rush out now. If
you do... my parents' sacrifice will be in vain.

\N<Yuia>I can't heed your advice...! If I overlook such a scene now,
I'd rather be dead...!
\N<Segi>...please. I'm still begging you.
\N<Yuia>Segi...!!

\N<Segi>As their daughter, my parents' determination and souls are
flowing into me. It's not a lie... I can feel it, I really
can.

\N<Segi>...it might be easier to just burst out here. But that's not
right. That's not what they want.

\N<Segi>If I did that... it would just be self-satisfaction. It
would make me an unfilial child... that's not acceptable.
\N<Yuia>Segi...

Segi's small hands were clenched tightly, so tightly that
they seemed to bleed.

With eyes wet from tears, she still managed to articulate
her words firmly.
The foolish one is... me. I was the one who was wrong.

The two people risking their lives right now to save me and
Segi in front of my eyes, Orugi and Seno... I knew of their
determination as well.
\N<Segi>...Lord Yuia.

\N<Yuia>...I understand. Indeed, if I were to foolishly show myself
now and get captured by them, it would render my parents'
determination and readiness all for naught. That would be...
just as you say, mere self-satisfaction.

\N<Yuia>I'm sorry... even though you're suffering many times more
than I am...
\N<Segi>...no.

\N<Yuia>I've decided... to become a coward. To use my subordinates
as bait to prolong my life, to become the lowest of cowards.

\N<Segi>You're not a coward. Both my parents and I... we understand.
We know the firmness of your clenched fist and... the warmth
of your tears.
\N<Yuia>Segi...
